President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has proclaimed October 9, 2023, as Leif Erikson Day in honor of the Nordic explorer who is believed to have been the first European to set foot in North America. The proclamation recognizes the contributions of Nordic Americans to the United States and celebrates their heritage. Nordic immigrants have played a significant role in American history, establishing communities, fighting for liberty, and contributing to various sectors such as education, business, and public service. The proclamation also highlights the strong relations between the United States and Nordic nations, emphasizing collaboration on challenges such as addressing the climate crisis and promoting security and humanitarian assistance. The proclamation concludes by calling upon all Americans to celebrate Nordic American contributions with appropriate ceremonies and activities.